title: Compound of 5-cube and 5-orthoplex
summary: In 5-dimensional geometry, the 5-cube 5-orthoplex compound[1] is a polytope compound composed of a regular 5-cube and dual regular 5-orthoplex.[2]  A compound polytope is a figure that is composed of several polytopes sharing a common center. The outer vertices of a compound can be connected to form a convex polytope called the convex hull. The compound is a facetting of the convex hull.
